- internal/service/homeassistant_test.go

### VideoQueue requirements
- Profiles: sd(848×480), hd(1280×720), fhd(1920×1080, snapshot-only)
- Stall detection: 15s without new H.264 frame → emit stall event, trigger restart
- Generation counter: increment on each restart so consumers can detect stream reset
- VideoEnabled bool field (used by ServiceManager for no-auto-stop exception)
- Light control: send light-on command via MqttQueue before snapshot

### FileTransferService requirements  
- GCode patching: call internal/gcode functions before upload
- Layer count extraction: call internal/gcode ExtractLayerCount
- File upload via PPPPService PPPP channel (Aabb frames)
- Progress callback: emit Notify with percentage 0-100
- On completion: return nil (do not restart)

### TimelapseService requirements
- Periodic snapshots via VideoQueue (interval from env TIMELAPSE_INTERVAL_SEC, default 30)
- Resume window: 60 min — if existing capture dir found within 60min, resume it
- Orphan recovery: up to 24h old capture dirs get recovered and assembled
- ffmpeg assembly: exec.Command("ffmpeg", ...) — framerate 10fps, output mp4
- Persistent frames with .meta sidecar file (JSON: started_at, printer_sn, filename)
- Max videos: TIMELAPSE_MAX_VIDEOS (default 10), prune oldest on exceed
- Light control modes: off/on/auto (auto = on during capture, off when idle)

### HomeAssistantService requirements
- External MQTT broker (HA_MQTT_HOST/PORT/USER/PASSWORD env vars)
- Publish HA Discovery payloads on connect:
  - 11 sensors: progress, state, filename, layer, speed, temp_nozzle, temp_bed, etc.
  - 2 binary sensors: online, door_open
  - 1 switch: light
  - 1 camera: snapshot
- LWT (Last Will Testament): availability topic set to offline on disconnect
- Heartbeat: publish availability=online every 60s
- Bidirectional light switch: subscribe to command topic, call MqttQueue light command

### Critical
- All goroutines respect context.Context
- WorkerRun must BLOCK — no busy-loops
- ffmpeg: use exec.CommandContext for cancellation
- Package: github.com/django1982/ankerctl/internal/service

### After completion
1. Run: go build ./... && go test -race ./internal/service/...
2. Fix ALL compilation errors
3. Write completion report to: docs/agents/reports/2026-03-05-phase9b-codex.md
   Use template from: docs/agents/COMPLETION_TEMPLATE.md

